    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style or culture of a Native American tribe in Maryland, whose historical lands comprise the Chesapeake Bay area. Today they are known as two different state-recognized bands, the "Piscataway-Conoy Tribe" and the "Piscataway Indian Nation."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
